node.text: How to know if you are overthinking it? Best selling author Michelle Rial chats with me about her creative slump, the shower principle, how framing is important, and her new book that’s kinda sad but maybe a little funny, but mostly sad. I promise you will find humor and comfort in Michelle’s simple yet complex translations of what being human feels like. Follow her @michellerial

node.text: For years I have been trying to fit emotions into one image. To locate something universally human. This year, I started a newsletter to explore the complex nature of thoughts and feelings, the things that are too complicated and messy to fit into one image - it’s called “bad at keeping secrets” it’s a newsletter with very little news. I hope it can be a conversation. That we can talk about what it feels like to be human in this moment.
